       PROCEDURE Excl(VAR set: ARRAY OF SET; i: LONGINT);
       PROCEDURE InclChar(VAR charset: CharSet; ch: CHAR);
       PROCEDURE ExclChar(VAR charset: CharSet; ch: CHAR);
       PROCEDURE Subset(set1, set2: ARRAY OF SET) : BOOLEAN;
       PROCEDURE Card(set: ARRAY OF SET) : INTEGER;


[1mDESCRIPTION[0m
       [4mSets[24m implements set operations for character sets and sets of arbitrary
       length.  [4msetsize[24m defines the number of bits per [1mSET [22mtype.   [4mCharSet[24m  is
       an  array of [1mSET [22msufficient for characters.  [4mInitSet[24m initializes [4mset[24m to
       the empty set.

       Following set operators are implemented:


       set operator   set operation
       ---------------------------------
       unary [1m-        [4m[22mComplement[0m
       [1m+              [4m[22mUnion[0m
       [1m-              [4m[22mDifference[0m
       [1m*              [4m[22mIntersection[0m
       [1m/              [4m[22mSymDifference[0m
       [1mIN             [4m[22mIn[24m and [4mCharIn[0m
       [1m=              [4m[22mEqual[0m
       [1mINCL           [4m[22mIncl[24m and [4mInclChar[0m
       [1mEXCL           [4m[22mExcl[24m and [4mExclChar[0m

       [4mSubset[24m returns [1mTRUE [22miff [4mset1[24m is contained in [4mset2[24m.   [4mCard[24m  returns  the
       cardinality (number of elements) of [4mset[24m.

[1mDIAGNOSTICS[0m
       Assertions of [4mSets[24m fail if the length of [4mresult[24m is less than the length
       of [4mset1[24m or [4mset2[24m.



